comments.body:
Regarding enableFastLaunch, I think we need to keep the command because we shouldn't require the RM to be restarted to update the dependency tarball in HDFS. It would be okay to make the RM do the upload automatically on start, but the command is still needed. If you add the following after instantiating the ServiceClient in ApiServiceClient, that should fix the issue.
{noformat}
    sc.init(getConfig());
    sc.start();
{noformat}

- config name for https is "webapp.https.address"
{code}
 String rmAddress = conf.get("yarn.resourcemanager.webapp.address");
    if(conf.getBoolean("hadoop.ssl.enabled", false)) {
      scheme = "https://";
    }
{code}

